subject: Add a jitter for check of time synchronization.
commit_message:
Add a jitter for check of time synchronization.

If a request time of check is smaller than a time diff (between local and remote
server) and that time diff is tolerable small then it still prints:
!! http://server:port/recon/time current time is 2016-07-05 06:24:02, but
remote is 2016-07-05 06:24:02, differs by 0.00 sec

So you can use a jitter option to consider it as time synchronized:
swift-recon -T --jitter 0.01

Change-Id: I4891397e7cc0817819201b361f79f8fe7fdcfc89

subject: Don't disable satellite repo after registration
commit_message:
Don't disable satellite repo after registration

Previously the rhel registration script disabled the satellite repo
after installing packages from it.  This means those packages will
never be updated, which is not desirable from a long-term
maintenance perspective.

I believe this behavior is a holdover from the dib registration
script, where we don't want to leave repos enabled because the
image may be deployed many times and each instance needs to be
re-registered.  In t-h-t we don't have that problem because the
script only runs at deploy time so it's okay and desirable to leave
the repos enabled.

Change-Id: I5d760467b458d90d74507a55effc49b71d22eaa3
Closes-Bug: 1673116

subject: Use configured admin creds in rbac utils
commit_message:
Use configured admin creds in rbac utils

Use ``get_configured_admin_credentials()`` in rbac_utils to instantiate
an admin client manager without having to rely on creating a new
set of credentials, which is problematic when using pre-provisioned
credentials. This is because rbac_utils consumes a set of credentials
allocated in the accounts.yaml file, which can cause tests to fail.

Using ``get_configured_admin_credentials()`` is a workaround because
it uses admin credentials specified in tempest's config's [auth]
section, which already exist in the system.

Change-Id: I0622bb057c365fdf652e4a110125678371ac4569

subject: Always start httpd at the same time
commit_message:
Always start httpd at the same time

Puppet wipes out whatever is not in it's resource catalog each run for
httpd. This causes httpd to restart if in the next step there are
reasources added that were not there earlier.

This patch, thus changes the instances of httpd to start at the same
time: On step 3 for the bootstrap node, and on step 4 for every other
node.

 Conflicts:
	manifests/profile/base/heat/api.pp
	manifests/profile/base/heat/api_cfn.pp
	manifests/profile/base/heat/api_cloudwatch.pp
	manifests/profile/base/horizon.pp
	manifests/profile/base/zaqar.pp

Closes-Bug: #1699502
Change-Id: I3d29728c1ab7bd5b78100f89e00e5fa082f97b0c
Co-Authored-By: Alex Schultz <aschultz@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit ad14f23c112922399b96601806da34ad045cbf22)

subject: 3PAR: Fixed image cache enabled capability.
commit_message:
3PAR: Fixed image cache enabled capability.

This patch fixes the problem with the 3PAR not
working with generic image cache during cache-miss scenario.

In order to do the image caching, the 3PAR has to create a
temporary snapshot of the volume being cloned.  Then the
background cloning is against the temporary snapshot.
The problem is, the temporary snapshot stays around.
We try to account for this temporary snapshot in
the delete volume action.

Addition to above scenario, When we try retype/migration of
above volume then this operation was unsuccessful as
temporary snapshot was present. So before doing retype/
migration of volume on 3par, we are checking temporary
snapshot on it, if it is present then we are deleting it.

Change-Id: I5eae88660b987d30c29a4827d349acc0350148bb
Closes-Bug: 1686985
(cherry picked from commit 00bdedafff783fa6ead0d9204f6e7c34be5ab2fc)

subject: Add 'tasks_api_access' policy
commit_message:
Add 'tasks_api_access' policy

The Tasks API was made admin-only in Mitaka to prevent it from being
exposed directly to end users.  The interoperable image import
process introduced in Pike uses the tasks engine to perform the
import.  This patch introduces a new policy, 'tasks_api_access',
that determines whether a user can make Tasks API calls.

The currently existing task-related policies are retained so that
operators can have fine-grained control over tasks.  With this
new policy, operators can restrict Tasks API access to admins,
while at the same time, admin-level credentials are not required
for glance to perform task-related functions on behalf of users.

Change-Id: I3f66f7efa7c377d999a88457fc6492701a894f34
Closes-bug: #1711468

subject: Cinder storage aggregate
commit_message:
Cinder storage aggregate

In a large-scale cloud, there are thousands of storage backends with
different features or something else, such as performance, available
and so on. Volume types for Cinder are equal to host aggregates for
Nova in a way, which are used to aggregate storage backends with different
features or something else. But some customized features are usually
configured in cinder.conf, so we have to restart cinder-volume service
for customized features changes. If we use storage aggregates, we can
use command line without restarting cinder-volume service.

Change-Id: I083a320cf896b35ff903564f583eeb15ab66a58e

commit_message:

Instead, use the common_settings file to source all the variables
we need at the early stages of devstack setup and during the upgrade
itself. This also fixes an issue with the networking-generic-switch
upgrade script, which is run from the old release instead of the new
one.

subject: cisco zone driver can't support multi-fabric with same vsan
commit_message:
cisco zone driver can't support multi-fabric with same vsan

If multi-fabric with different ip have the same zoning_vsan, device_map
only return the last fabric's fabric_map. This may lead to missing other
fabric_map.In line 171, we change device_map[zoning_vsan] = fabric_map to
device_map[fabric_name] = fabric_map, which may correct the problem.

cinder/zonemanager/drivers/cisco/cisco_fc_san_lookup_service.py：

74     def get_device_mapping_from_network(self,
75                                         initiator_wwn_list,
76                                         target_wwn_list):
......
114         if fabrics:
......
121             for fabric_name in fabrics:
......
171                 device_map[zoning_vsan] = fabric_map
......
173         return device_map

cinder.conf
[DEFAULT]
......
[fc-zone-manager]
......
fc_fabric_names = CISCO_FABRIC_A,CISCO_FABRIC_B
......
[CISCO_FABRIC_A]
......
cisco_fc_fabric_address = IP_A
cisco_zoning_vsan = same_vsan

[CISCO_FABRIC_B]
......
cisco_fc_fabric_address = IP_B
cisco_zoning_vsan = same_vsan

Change-Id: I02a719d3ba724c0eb6c468062d648b243f62e08e
Closes-Bug: #1704143

subject: Fix bug creating port in different projects fail in Admin panel
commit_message:
Fix bug creating port in different projects fail in Admin panel

Prfeviously network_get() in Neutron API wrapper has a hard-coded
condition to retrieve subnet details. This causes a failure of
creating a port in a network owned by a different project in
the admin panel.

This commit changes the logic of network_get() to try to retrieve
subnet details as much as possible instead of applying a hard-coded
condition. It allows us to avoid mirroring the neutron behavior.

There are some cases where subnet detail cannot be retrieved.
If such case, the Neutron API wrapper now drops such subnets.
Returning only subnet ID(s) sounds meaningless in GUI perspective
and it is already done in network_list().

Change-Id: I7d1860c2748521dd2dc394dc2484d7d7570d4bb8
Closes-Bug: #1645708

subject: Windows: ensure exec calls don't block other greenthreads
commit_message:
Windows: ensure exec calls don't block other greenthreads

eventlet.green.subprocess is not actually greenthread friendly on
Windows. It just uses the native subprocess.Popen in this case.

For this reason, exec calls do not yield on Windows, blocking other
greenthreads.

This change avoids this issue by wrapping the 'communicate' call
using eventlet.tpool.

We're also ensuring that subprocess.Popen uses *native* threads
internally in order to avoid deadlocks when passing data through
stdin.

Change-Id: Ic25fd1b61b5498f16e6049cbbe0877492f8aab4d
Closes-Bug: #1709586

subject: 3PAR: Fixed image cache enabled capability.
commit_message:
3PAR: Fixed image cache enabled capability.

This patch fixes the problem with the 3PAR not
working with generic image cache during cache-miss scenario.

In order to do the image caching, the 3PAR has to create a
temporary snapshot of the volume being cloned.  Then the
background cloning is against the temporary snapshot.
The problem is, the temporary snapshot stays around.
We try to account for this temporary snapshot in
the delete volume action.

Addition to above scenario, When we try retype/migration of
above volume then this operation was unsuccessful as
temporary snapshot was present. So before doing retype/
migration of volume on 3par, we are checking temporary
snapshot on it, if it is present then we are deleting it.

Change-Id: I5eae88660b987d30c29a4827d349acc0350148bb
Closes-Bug: 1686985

subject: Apply for stable:follows-policy for Kolla
commit_message:
Apply for stable:follows-policy for Kolla

The Kolla core reviewer team unanimously [1] voted to apply for the
stable:follows-policy tag.  I recognize there may be some reluctance
to accept our application because of the unnatural activities that
took place to correct a fatal flaw in Kolla Liberty.

The Kolla core team is committed to following the stable backports
policy including:
1. master first
2. only high and critical bug fixes permitted
3. Absolutely no feature backports
4. Absolutely no ABI changes
5. Absolutely no breaking config file changes

Further, A team has been formed to execute the stable backport process
for Kolla consisting of:

Michal Jastrzebski (inc0)
Paul Bourke (pbourke)
Dave Walker (davewalker) - stable maintenance core and backport team mentor
Jeffrey Zhang (jeffrey4l)
Eduardo Gonzalez (egonzalez)

Kolla is in active maintenance.  The backport team has committed to actively
maintain Kolla on a 45 day schedule (or whatever is convienient for the
release team if they are overloaded at the time).

This includes:
1. Following the review guidelines
2. Proactively identifying and backporting high and critical bug fixes
3. Keeping the backport backlog to a minimum.
4. 45 day zstream release schedule - low rate of change critical or
   high defects only
5. Constantly improving our CI systems and monitoring the stable
   branches CI systems.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-July/099902.html

Change-Id: Ib2a1039120607859ffa10f597e49577b41a90e17

subject: Fix flakey EC frag duplication policy test
commit_message:
Fix flakey EC frag duplication policy test

Fixes test_GET_with_duplicate_but_sufficient_frag_indexes
failing intermittently.

The original non-duplicated-frags version of the test in
TestECObjController verified that the controller would search all
primaries, ignoring repeated fragment indexes and finally find the
last necessary unique fragment on the first handoff. The version of
the test for a duplicated fragments policy in
TestECDuplicationObjController had the final necessary fragment on the
first of the 'duplicate' primaries (index ec_num_unique_fragments + 1)
so there was a chance that it would be found before all of the first
ec_num_unique_fragments had been tried, causing the test to fail as
reported in the linked bug report.

This patch moves the final necessary unique fragment to the first
handoff (index 2 * index ec_num_unique_fragments + 1) and aligns the
test with the intent of the equivalent test in TestECObjController,
so that the two tests can be moved to a single implementation in an
inherited mixin.

test_GET_with_duplicate_but_insufficient_frag is also moved to the
new mixin since the two implementations of that test were also very
similar.

Change-Id: I4d99dea8e941bccb6fa610bab39e38a6976a3721
Closes-Bug: #1710951

subject: Automatically retry introspection for failing nodes
commit_message:
Automatically retry introspection for failing nodes

After the first pass of introspection has finished, retry introspection
on all the failed nodes.

Users can pass in `max_retry_attempts` to change the behaviour. Passing
`1` will mean nodes will retry introspection once etc. Passing 0 will
disable retrying.

Users can also use `node_timeout` to customise how long the workflow
waits for nodes to finish introspection before aborting and retrying
them.

subject: Containerize Manila Share for HA
commit_message:
Containerize Manila Share for HA

This service allows configuring and deploying manila-share
containers in a HA overcloud managed by pacemaker.

The containers are managed and run by pacemaker. Pacemaker runs the
standard Kolla image but overrides the initial command so that
it explicitely calls manila-share. This way, we shield ourselves
from any unexpected future change in Kolla.
This container needs to use the 'docker_config' section to invoke
puppet (as opposed to 'docker_puppet_tasks'), because due to the HA
composability each resource creation needs to happen on the bootstrap
node of that service and 'docker_puppet_tasks' will only run on the
controller/primary role.

Based on work done in fdb233e64e3d78014dd7e351abfed5aec5035866

Gnocchi as a storage backend for resource and metric
data.

Configure ceilometer to use the gnocchi dispatcher
in the event that ceilometer is related to gnocchi.
This has the side effect of disabling the ceilometer
API - Aodh and Gnocchi API's should be used directly
in this deployment topology.

Note that Gnocchi is only supported in OpenStack
Mitaka or later; 'metrics-service' is added to the
required interfaces configuration as an alternative
to 'mongodb' for >= Mitaka.

Change-Id: Ia31dfefd5efa3fb5ec2ba5d132ee865c567bd8df

subject: objects: exclude revision_number from updatable fields
commit_message:
objects: exclude revision_number from updatable fields

Revision service plugin is the entity that updates the database model
attribute, and we don't allow to modify the attribute on API layer. We
should not allow to explicitly update it on OVO layer either.

This can help with spurious unit test failures that sometimes try to
update revision number and then reuse the same number to fetch the
object. If revision service plugin decides to bump the number during the
test case execution once more, using the old number may yield no
results.

Conflicts:
	neutron/objects/extensions/standardattributes.py

Closes-Bug: #1694753
Change-Id: I4666c672223ac38508738b739207f754847c62bc

subject: Handle addition of new nodes/instances in ironic flavor migration
commit_message:
Handle addition of new nodes/instances in ironic flavor migration

The original idea for ironic flavor migration was to handle it in
init_host(), so that the code wouldn't run often. But in a situation
like an upgrade with multiple Nova computes handling ironic nodes, this
may not cover all the nodes, so we are moving it to be run whenever the
cache is refreshed, and new nodes for the compute service that have
instances are detected. We also need to cover the cases where an
existing node has a new instance created on it to ensure that that new
instance's flavor is also migrated.

Closes-Bug: #1707021

subject: Add stestr to global requirements
commit_message:
Add stestr to global requirements

stestr is a fork of testrepository, designed specifically to concentrate
on being a dedicated test runner.[1] Testrepository is used everywhere for
testing in openstack but is not being maintained at all. The last patch
(which wasn't fixing the broken ci config) was on Dec. 6 2016, but it
hasn't been released. I also had several patches up for review that went
years without any progress. [2][3] Having such a critical piece of our
testing infrastructure isn't maintainable situation. stestr was forked
primarily because of the lack of activity in testr, and it fixes a lot
of longstanding bugs and usability issues and is actively maintained. I
also wrote it to try and be simpler to maintain, the testrepository
codebase was hard to contribute to. (at least for me) So I tried to make
the interfaces as straightforward and explicit. The long term plan is to
get everything onto stestr and stop using testrepository for testing in
OpenStack. But in the short term I have patches up to switch os-testr
under the covers [4] and start migrating some projects [5][6] before
making the big push to switch everything.

[Q] Is the library actively maintained?
[A] Yes.

[Q] Is the library good code?
[A] Yes.

[Q] Is the library python 3 compatible?
[A] Yes.

[Q] Is the library license compatible?
[A] Yes. Apache 2.0.

[Q] Is the library already packaged in the distros we target
    (Ubuntu latest / Fedora latest)?
[A] No.

[Q] Is the function of this library already covered by other
    libraries in global-requirements.txt?
[A] No.

[Q] Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev
    or infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes,
    of course) Which?
[A] Yes, as described above.

[1] https://github.com/mtreinish/stestr
[2] https://github.com/testing-cabal/testrepository/pull/16
[3] https://github.com/testing-cabal/testrepository/pull/19
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/488441/
[5] https://review.openstack.org/491035
[6] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/491074/

Change-Id: I2c7618a742439fd2ed26879f3114f0f66fd6337f
